HEADWORD: Acheron
<hw>Ach"e*ron</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Myth.)</fld> <def>A river in the Nether World or
infernal regions; also, the infernal regions themselves. By some of the
English poets it was supposed to be a flaming lake or gulf.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

